  <section class="info info-process">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="info-head"><div class="mono-label">Our process</div><h2>What happens between &quot;drop-off&quot; and &quot;fixed&quot;.</h2><p>Four stages. No grey area. You'll know where your Mac is at every step &mdash; we send timestamped photos from the bench when the display comes off.</p></div>
      <ol class="process-grid">
        <li class="process-step"><div class="process-step-head"><span class="process-step-num">01</span><span class="process-step-time">30 min</span></div><h3>Free Pre-diagnosis</h3><p>Walk in or ship your MacBook. We inspect the display, test backlight channels on the scope, and check for related damage &mdash; hinge flex, logic board shorts, Stage Light. You get a written quote before anything is opened.</p></li>
        <li class="process-step"><div class="process-step-head"><span class="process-step-num">02</span><span class="process-step-time">1-2 days</span></div><h3>Repair on the bench</h3><p>Work happens in our Fitzrovia workshop &mdash; never sent out. Screen assemblies are replaced with the hinge and antenna transferred to the new unit; backlight IC replacements are done under a stereo microscope with lead-free solder.</p></li>
        <li class="process-step"><div class="process-step-head"><span class="process-step-num">03</span><span class="process-step-time">45 min</span></div><h3>Calibration &amp; QA</h3><p>Every repair is True Tone calibrated against a reference sensor, colour-profile matched, and run through a 30-point QA pass &mdash; brightness uniformity, touch-bar response, keyboard, speakers, camera, Wi-Fi throughput.</p></li>
        <li class="process-step"><div class="process-step-head"><span class="process-step-num">04</span><span class="process-step-time">Same day</span></div><h3>Collection or courier</h3><p>Collect in person (Mon-Fri) or opt for insured next-day courier back to you. Every repair ships with a printed QA report, the 2-year warranty card, and the original parts if you want them returned.</p></li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="info info-parts">
    <div class="container info-parts-grid">
      <div class="info-parts-text"><div class="mono-label">Parts &amp; materials</div><h2>Genuine Apple displays, recalibrated in-house.</h2><p>Aftermarket &quot;compatible&quot; screens cost less up front and fail inside 18 months &mdash; lower brightness, off-white point, dead True Tone. We don't fit them. Every screen we install is a genuine Apple assembly, tested against a reference panel, and warrantied for two years.</p><dl class="info-parts-dl"><dt>Source</dt><dd>Genuine Apple LCD &amp; OLED assemblies &mdash; reclaimed from donor devices, not aftermarket.</dd><dt>Calibration</dt><dd>Every display factory-matched for colour temperature, gamma, and True Tone before it leaves the bench.</dd><dt>What's new</dt><dd>LCD panel, backlight driver, digitizer cable, hinge covers, adhesive perimeter. Camera and antenna transferred.</dd><dt>What's recycled</dt><dd>Your original LCD is stripped for recoverable components. You can request the carcass back at collection.</dd></dl></div>
      <div class="info-parts-card"><div class="info-parts-card-top"><span class="mono-label" style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);">Supply chain</span><span class="info-badge">Verified</span></div><div class="info-parts-chain"><div class="info-parts-node"><div class="info-parts-node-title">Genuine display assemblies</div><div class="info-parts-node-body">Original LCD / mini-LED assemblies, tested and sealed.</div></div><div class="info-parts-arrow" aria-hidden="true">&darr;</div><div class="info-parts-node"><div class="info-parts-node-title">Recalibration bench</div><div class="info-parts-node-body">White-point, gamma, True Tone profile flashed.</div></div><div class="info-parts-arrow" aria-hidden="true">&darr;</div><div class="info-parts-node"><div class="info-parts-node-title">Your MacBook</div><div class="info-parts-node-body">Fitted, QA'd, returned with a 2-year warranty.</div></div></div></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="info info-warranty">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="info-head"><div class="mono-label">Warranty &amp; standards</div><h2>Two years of cover. No asterisks.</h2><p>Apple's own out-of-warranty screen repair runs 90 days. Most London repair shops offer 6 or 12 months. We warrant every MacBook screen we fit for 24 months &mdash; parts, labour, and any re-work.</p></div>
      <div class="warranty-grid"><div class="warranty-card"><div class="warranty-num">24 mo</div><div class="warranty-label">Warranty period</div><div class="warranty-body">Against functional defect of the display assembly we fitted. Covers parts, labour, and return shipping.</div></div><div class="warranty-card"><div class="warranty-num">0</div><div class="warranty-label">Excess on re-work</div><div class="warranty-body">If anything we touched fails inside warranty, we fix it free. No diagnostic fee, no &quot;goodwill&quot; bargaining.</div></div><div class="warranty-card"><div class="warranty-num">48 h</div><div class="warranty-label">Warranty turnaround</div><div class="warranty-body">Priority bench slot if a warrantied repair fails. Drop in or use our pre-paid courier label.</div></div><div class="warranty-card"><div class="warranty-num">ISO 9001</div><div class="warranty-label">Workshop standard</div><div class="warranty-body">Repair log, torque spec, calibration reference for every job. Corporate clients get the audit trail on request.</div></div></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="faq">
    <div class="container faq-grid">
      <div class="faq-left"><div class="mono-label">Frequently asked</div><h2>Questions, answered honestly.</h2><p>If you want to speak to a human first, call <a href="tel:+442070998517">+44 (0)207 099 8517</a> or drop in &mdash; we're opposite The London Palladium.</p></div>
      <div class="faq-right"><div class="faq-item open"><div class="faq-q">How long does a MacBook screen repair take?<span class="icon">+</span></div><div class="faq-a">Most screen repairs are completed in 1-2 working days. If you drop in before 11am and we have the part in stock, same-day turnaround is often possible. Walk-ins welcome at our Fitzrovia workshop &mdash; no appointment needed for diagnosis.</div></div><div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Are the replacement screens genuine Apple parts?<span class="icon">+</span></div><div class="faq-a">Yes. We source original Apple displays, reclaim them where possible, and recalibrate every unit in-house to original factory standards. That means True Tone, full brightness, and colour accuracy are preserved.</div></div><div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Is my data safe during the repair?<span class="icon">+</span></div><div class="faq-a">Completely. Screen repairs don't touch your drive, but we run a GDPR-compliant workshop and sign an NDA on request for corporate clients. We never ask for your passcode unless post-repair testing requires it &mdash; and you can be present for that step.</div></div><div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">What does the 2-year warranty cover?<span class="icon">+</span></div><div class="faq-a">Every MacBook screen repair carries a full 2-year warranty against functional defects. The warranty covers the replaced display, the labour, and any re-work needed during that period. Accidental damage isn't covered, but we'll always quote fairly for re-repairs.</div></div><div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Do I need to book, or can I just walk in?<span class="icon">+</span></div><div class="faq-a">Either works. Walk in Mon-Fri 9am-6pm (Fri until 6pm, closed weekends) for a free diagnosis and written quote before any work starts. Booking ahead reserves a workshop slot and is usually faster.</div></div><div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">You're microsoldering specialists. What does that mean?<span class="icon">+</span></div><div class="faq-a">Most repair shops swap whole components. We work at the board level: individual chips, resistors, and solder joints under a microscope. That's why other repair shops and insurers send their tougher cases to us.</div></div></div>
    </div>
  </section>

